# Difference between focused and diffuse modes of thinking

The modes are mutually exclusive.

## Focused

* Narrowing the attention of the brain's energies to a smaller field, which
  allows for exploring something in detail at the cost of being able
  to take a broader view of things.

## Diffuse

* A more relaxed mode which casts the mind's attention wider, to allow
  for new connections to be made and new ideas to be formed.

